# Design a REST API

@model claude-opus-4-6

@role :architect(API)

@context {
  Stack: Node.js, Express, PostgreSQL, Redis
  Auth: JWT with refresh tokens
  API style: RESTful with JSON:API conventions
  Versioning: URL-based (/v1/)
}

@task {
  Design the API endpoints for the given feature.
  For each endpoint provide:
  - Method + path
  - Request body / query params
  - Response shape (TypeScript interface)
  - Status codes
  - Auth requirements
  - Rate limiting tier
}

@constraint Follow JSON:API spec for error responses.
@constraint Use plural nouns for resource names.
@constraint Include pagination for all list endpoints.

@output format: markdown
